tier_min: pro
complexity: medium
context: [solo]
persona_hints: ["P4"]

intent: |
  From the initial trigger to the closed outcome described in scope, deliver every artefact named in success_criteria without skipping the decision gates between stages.

scope: |
  Given a discovery brief, produce two defensible quotes (fixed-price and T&M) with an expli
  cit AI-leverage adjustment and a regulatory-uncertainty buffer. 'Done' = client receives b
  oth options, internal margin model is documented, and post-mortem can replay assumptions.

summary: "Fixed-Price vs T&M Estimation with AI Risk Buffer — Given a discovery brief, produce two defensible quotes (fixed-price and T&M) with an explicit AI-leverage adjustment and a regulatory-uncertainty..."

success_criteria:
  - "Every stage's decision gate is recorded as passed before the next stage starts."
  - "All artefacts named in the stage outputs are produced and signed off."
  - "A written close-out record exists for archival and post-mortem."

token_budget_estimate: 15000

stages:
  - name: "Scope"
    intent: "Define the scope, exit criteria, and the people who must agree on success."
    tasks:
      - "Restate the scope outcome for this engagement in one sentence."
      - "Identify who owns the scope output and who must approve it."
      - "Produce the scope artefact in the agreed format."
    methodologies:
      - slug: cost-estimation
        path: pro/pm/pm-traditional/cost-estimation
        required: true
        tier_gate: pro
    outputs:
      - "Scope artefact (written, signed off)"
      - "Updated decision log entry for the scope step"
    decision_gate: "Advance to the next stage when the scope artefact is approved by the named owner; iterate if any blocker remains."
  - name: "Discovery"
